.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:6:Now I need: the scorer's `evaluateRouteGold` signature, the `_args.cjs` surface, and what route-gold artifacts exist per-hub (the gold source the lane would assert parity against).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:34:- **F-2-4 Spec-tree resolver coupling (P1, novel).** `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` resolves the resolver from `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`. Specs are mutable planning artifacts; any rename of 011-runtime-engine (sk-doc packets restructure often) silently breaks the resolver, `compiled-route.cjs:36-39` catches and returns the legacy sentinel, and the lane goes vacuously green. The lane MUST pre-flight that path's existence and surface breakage as drift, not parity.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:35:- **F-2-5 Hub-type vs compiled-eligibility mismatch (P2, novel).** `isHubTypeSkill` (run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68) keys off `hub-router.json` (7 hubs have one). Compiled-serving eligibility is keyed off the activation manifest *plus* the `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` allowlist in `advisor-recommend.ts`. A hub can have route-gold auto-on while being compiled-N/A. The lane MUST distinguish `n/a (not compiled-eligible)` from `drift`, otherwise N/A hubs get scored as either false-pass or false-fail.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:39:2. **Build the lane around a `compiledParity` status enum**: `{match, drift, vacuous, n/a, resolver-missing}` â€” only `match` is a pass; `vacuous` and `resolver-missing` are hard failures (the trap states), `drift` is a real regression, `n/a` is informational.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:41:4. **Assert the resolver path + manifest state in `compiled-parity.cjs`'s pre-flight**, before any scenario loop â€” fail loud on spec-tree drift, never fail safe.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:46:  {"id":"F-2-2","area":"benchmark","finding":"Vacuous-parity trap: SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 alone is insufficient. resolve.cjs:41-42 requires the per-hub activation manifest to read servingAuthority==='compiled'; otherwise resolveRoute returns null and compiled-route.cjs:39 emits a legacy sentinel that a naive lane reads as 'compiled matches legacy'.","evidence":"resolve.cjs:41-42 (flagEnabled AND servingAuthority!=='compiled'); compiled-route.cjs:36-39 (catchâ†’legacy sentinel); .opencode/specs/.../010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.json shows servingAuthority:'compiled' (so sk-code is the valid pilot; other hubs may still be 'legacy')","severity":"P0","actionable":"compiled-parity.cjs pre-flight MUST read 010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json and treat servingAuthority!=='compiled' as status 'vacuous' (hard fail), never a pass; document the dual gate in the lane README.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:48:  {"id":"F-2-4","area":"archiving","finding":"Spec-tree resolver coupling: compiled-route.cjs:16-21 resolves the resolver from inside .opencode/specs/.../011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs. Specs are mutable planning artifacts; a rename silently breaks the resolver and the catch at compiled-route.cjs:36-39 returns the legacy sentinel, producing vacuous parity. ZERO activation/manifest.json or compiled/route-gold.typed.json live under .opencode/skills/<hub>/ â€” all 19 + 12 live under specs only.","evidence":"compiled-route.cjs:16-21 (path.resolve into specs/); find results: 19 activation/manifest.json + 12 route-gold.typed.json ALL under .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-.../007-unified-refactor-implementation/, ZERO under .opencode/skills/<hub>/","severity":"P1","actionable":"compiled-parity.cjs pre-flight asserts the resolver path exists (fs.existsSync) AND skills-tree activation archive exists; recommend a follow-up to copy per-hub activation/manifest.json + compiled/route-gold.typed.json into .opencode/skills/<hub>/activation/ + compiled/ as the durable serving source (closes named gap #4 for the benchmark's reliance).","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:49:  {"id":"F-2-5","area":"benchmark","finding":"Hub-type detection (isHubTypeSkill, run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68 keys on hub-router.json) is misaligned with compiled-serving eligibility (keys on activation manifest + advisor-recommend.ts COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS allowlist). A hub can have --route-gold auto-on while compiled-parity is structurally N/A.","evidence":"run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68-70 (isHubTypeSkill=fs.existsSync hub-router.json); 7 hubs have hub-router.json; resolve.cjs:42 serving authority is per-hub and independent","severity":"P2","actionable":"compiled-parity.cjs returns status enum {match|drift|vacuous|n/a|resolver-missing}; the orchestrator's verdict switch treats only match as pass, drift/vacuous/resolver-missing as failures, and n/a as informational (no verdict impact) so non-compiled hubs don't false-fail.","novelty":"new"}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:9:| `compiled-routing/flag-off-kill-switch.md` | Flag absent or `0` | Legacy `skillId`/`workflowMode` remain unchanged; `compiledRoute` is absent; status reports `legacy-fallback` with cause `flag-disabled`. |
