.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:12:| `compiled-routing/serving-status-classification.md` | Seven-hub fleet readout | Every hub reports exactly `compiled-serving`, `legacy-fallback`, or `drifted`, including cause, manifest identity, policy hash, and generation. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:22:The serving-status scenario also needs a new causal interface. Today missing/unparseable manifests become `legacy` (`011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:26-33`), while flag-off, legacy authority, and engine failure all collapse to `null` (`011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:40-47`) and finally the same legacy sentinel (`011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:64-65`). A manual playbook cannot distinguish kill-switch behavior from drift or breakage until a machine-readable status probe preserves the cause.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:30:The model and effort are valid (`cli-codex/SKILL.md:235-242`), and the CLI contract requires explicit model, effort, and service tier (`cli-codex/SKILL.md:267-268`). Keep routing validation read-only and tell LUNA to return the injected advisor skill, compiled action, target mode/packet, and serving status without executing the underlying user task. Treat timeout as `SKIP` with an infrastructure blocker, not routing failure: earlier LUNA routing runs hit the existing 150-second ceiling repeatedly (`010-live-activation/real-model/run-log.txt:50-57`, `:95-102`, `:143-150`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:34:1. P0 â€” carry `compiledRoute` and serving status through the prompt-time hook; otherwise LUNA never sees the decision being tested.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:35:2. P0 â€” expose causal serving status and an injectable disposable-workspace fixture path for drift testing.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:40:7. P1 â€” extend the named alignment gate: `verify_alignment_drift.py` currently scans language files and dispatches extension-specific checks (`sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py:480-515`), while the router contract it must protect lives in Markdown `RESOURCE_MAP` (`sk-code/code-opencode/SKILL.md:43-51`). It presently cannot prove parent/child router-map equality.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:45:  {"id":"F-3-2","area":"playbooks","finding":"The minimal canonical state corpus is four scenarios covering flag-off, flag-on fresh, drift-to-legacy, and causal seven-hub serving status.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:17","severity":"P0","actionable":"Create a compiled-routing category in the system-skill-advisor playbook with four per-feature files and exact JSON, exit-code, hook, and verdict evidence.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:46:  {"id":"F-3-3","area":"unnamed","finding":"The prompt-time hook cannot machine-enforce compiled routing because its recommendation type and rendered brief discard compiledRoute.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/lib/subprocess.ts:16","severity":"P0","actionable":"Carry compiled action, targets, and serving status through the hook subprocess contract and render them into the injected advisor brief before running LUNA scenarios.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:49:  {"id":"F-3-6","area":"activation","finding":"The current legacy sentinel collapses flag-disabled, missing or malformed manifest, legacy authority, and engine failure, so a serving-status playbook cannot classify cause.","evidence":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:40","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add a machine-readable per-hub status probe returning compiled-serving, legacy-fallback, or drifted plus a stable cause code, hash, and generation.","novelty":"refines:F-2-4"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:51:  {"id":"F-3-8","area":"sk-code-align","finding":"The named verify_alignment_drift.py gate checks language files but does not inspect the Markdown RESOURCE_MAP whose parent-child equality it is expected to enforce.","evidence":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py:480","severity":"P0","actionable":"Extend the verifier or add a companion check that parses code-opencode RESOURCE_MAP and fails when the sk-code parent projection diverges.","novelty":"new"}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:8:**Headline:** Promote compiled-vs-legacy evidence as per-hub Lane C run pairs under `.opencode/skills/<hub>/benchmark/<run-label>/`; do not copy `route-gold.typed.json` or activation artifacts out of the spec tree as standalone â€śresults.â€ť The storage contract allows only `skill-benchmark-report.json`, its rendered `.md`, and an optional per-run `README.md` ([storage guide:120-148](.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:120-148)); the parity result therefore belongs in a report-level `compiledRouting` block, as already planned ([014 spec:132-137](.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:132-137)).
